        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Mercantile Library Sept 2&#58; 84<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. Morais&#45;&#45;<lb/>
                Dear Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>I called at your<lb/> residence yesterday to ask you<lb/> for a little information&#44; and<lb/> as I did not find you&#44; may I<lb/> present my request by Note&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>I desire to know what are<lb/> the liturgical forms&#44; given in<lb/> your standards&#44; of Blessing to <lb/> be pronounced over different<lb/> classes of food or other re&#45;<lb/>freshments. For example&#45;&#45;<lb/> over <hi rend="underline">grapes</hi>&#8212;would the lan&#45;&#45;<lb/>guage be &#34;<hi rend="underline">The fruit of the vine</hi>&#34;&#63;<lb/> What I wish to show &#40;if it is<lb/> true&#41; is&#8212;that this language<lb/> does <hi rend="underline">not</hi> indicate&#44; where used<lb/> over wine&#44; that the article is<lb/> any other than regular <hi rend="underline">wine</hi>.<lb/></p> 
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I have supposed&#8212;am I <lb/> in error&#63;&#45;&#45; that over grapes<lb/> the liturgical form would<lb/> not be &#45;&#45;&#34;fruit of the vine&#59;&#34; and<lb/> that if&#44; under any circum&#45;<lb/>stances&#44; the fresh unfermented<lb/> juice of the grape should be<lb/> placed upon the table&#44; the<lb/> prescribed form would <hi rend="underline">not</hi><lb/> contain the language&#45;&#45;&#34;<hi rend="underline">fruit</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">of the vine</hi>.&#34; Will you do me<lb/> the favor to give me the infor&#45;<lb/>mation which I need&#63;</p>
            <p>I am by no means op&#45;<lb/>posed to any <hi rend="underline">true</hi> methods<lb/> of promoting Temperance&#59;<lb/> but I have kept up a pretty<lb/> steady fight against repre&#45;<lb/>sentations and arguments<lb/> which I consider baseless.<lb/></p>
            <p>In making application<lb/> to you for information&#44; it<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>is proper to say that I should<lb/> not think of using your <hi rend="underline">name</hi><lb/> in any publication&#44; until I<lb/> had distinct permission from<lb/> yourself.<lb/></p>
            <p>Accept my thanks for<lb/> your readiness&#44; in the past&#44;<lb/> to reply to my inquiries.<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours with much respect&#44;<lb/>
                S.C. Brace.<lb/></p>
            <p><hi rend="underline">At the Mercantile</hi> <hi rend="underline">Library</hi>&#44;<lb/>
                10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St.<lb/></p>
        </body>
